        // This is a standard result for this type of problem.
        // The $n$-th element (0-indexed $a_{n-1}$) and $(n+1)$-th element (0-indexed $a_n$) are the two "middle" elements of the entire $2n$ sorted array.
        // Any other pair of elements $a_i, a_j$ with $i < n-1$ or $j > n$ would result in a larger difference.
        //
