        // The median of Class 2 is $a_{n + (n-1)/2}$.
        // The difference is $a_{n+(n-1)/2} - a_{(n-1)/2}$. This is not $a_n - a_{n-1}$.
        //
        // The problem is asking for the minimum possible absolute difference.
        // The crucial observation is that if we sort all $2n$ students, $a_0, a_1, \dots, a_{2n-1}$,
        // then the two medians must be $a_{n-1}$ and $a_n$.
        //
        // Why? Suppose the two medians are $m_1$ and $m_2$.
        // Let $m_1 < m_2$.
        // $m_1$ is the $(k_1+1)$-th element of $C_1$. So there are $k_1$ elements in $C_1$ smaller than $m_1$.
        // $m_2$ is the $(k_2+1)$-th element of $C_2$. So there are $k_2$ elements in $C_2$ smaller than $m_2$.
